Australia Defeats Sri Lanka by 125 Runs in Opening Cricket Test

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-09-03T11:43:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-03/australia-closes-in-on-victory-in-opening-test-against-sri-lanka.html
Australia  defeated Sri Lanka by 125
runs in their opening cricket Test in Galle.  Ryan Harris took 5-62 as Sri Lanka was dismissed for 253 on
day four after being set a victory total of 379. Mahela
Jayawardene was top scorer for the host with 105, his 29th Test
century, while Angelo Mathews had 95.  Ricky Ponting, replaced as Australia captain by Michael
Clarke in March, is returning home tonight for the birth of his
second child and will miss the second Test, which begins Sept.
8, Cricket Australia said in a statement. Pointing, whoâ€™ll be
replaced by  David Warner , hopes to return for the final Test,
which starts Sept. 16.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
